Voi and Taveta will soon acquire town status after meeting all the requirements needed in law, Taita Taveta Governor John Mruttu (pictured) has announced. The two will be gazetted after meeting the criteria set by the Urban and Cities Act No 13 of 2011.Speaking at his Wundanyi office during a meeting to confirm the status of the towns, Mruttu assured residents that the new status will not affect taxes.Voi and Taveta towns have developed fast following improvements in infrastructure. The standard gauge railway has contributed to the growth of Voi town, while the Voi -Taveta-Holili road has boosted business in the border town.On boundaries, the governor said Taveta will cover the whole subcounty, while Voi will include Mbololo, as part of the municipality.